public class UnOrderedList
extends List
Description:

UnOrderedList encapsulates an UL list element in HTML

Instructions:

Use this class whenever you need to present the user with a list of items (without order)

Example: 

// Create an UnOrdered List
UnOrderedList ul = new UnOrderedList();
ul.addItem(new SimpleItem("UnOrdered1"));
ul.addItem(new SimpleItem("UnOrdered2"));
ul.addItem(new SimpleItem("UnOrdered3"));
